ciscoGsp2MIB.name: ciscoGsp2MIB

ciscoGsp2MIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems, Inc Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ss7@cisco.com
ciscoGsp2MIB.description: The MIB for providing information specified in ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network. This information can be used to manage messages transported over SS7 Network via Cisco IP Transfer Point. The Cisco IP Transfer Point (ITP) is a hardware and software solution that transports SS7 traffic using IP. Each ITP node provides function similar to SS7 signalling point. The relevant ITU documents describing this technology is the ITU Q series, including ITU Q.700: Introduction to CCITT signalling System No. 7 and ITU Q.701 Functional description of the message transfer part (MTP) of signalling System No. 7. The ITP Quality of Service (QoS) model allows the definition of 8 QoS classes, 0 through 7. QoS classes can be assigned only SCTP links. Only one QoS class can be assigned to an SCTP link. Class 0 will be designated as the default class. Packets that are not classified to a designated QoS class will get assigned to the default class. Each provisioned QoS class can be assigned an IP precedence value or a Differential Services Code Point (DSCP). The default class is initialized to IP precedence zero (0). The default class initial TOS setting can be changed through the command line interface. The Type of Service (TOS) byte in the IP header will be set to the IP precedence or DSCP that is assigned to class. Every packet forwarded over an SCTP link that was provisioned for a given QoS class will have the TOS byte set.

Cgsp2TcQosClass.name: Cgsp2TcQosClass
Cgsp2TcQosClass.description: The quality of service classification to be assigned to the IP packets used to transport the SS7 messages. Zero is a special value and is reserved to carry all traffic that does not specify a Qos or when exact match of the specified Qos is not available.

Cgsp2EventIndex.name: Cgsp2EventIndex
Cgsp2EventIndex.description: A monotonically increasing integer for the sole purpose of indexing events. When it reaches the maximum value the agent flushes the event table and wraps the value back to 1. Where lower values represent older entries and higher values represent newer entries.

CItpTcContextId.name: CItpTcContextId
CItpTcContextId.description: Each context is assigned an unique identifier starting with one and are monotonically increased by one.

cgsp2EventTable.name: cgsp2EventTable
cgsp2EventTable.description: A table used to provide information about all types of events on a signalling point.

cgsp2EventTableEntry.name: cgsp2EventTableEntry
cgsp2EventTableEntry.description: A table of SS7 events generated and received by a specific signalling point.

cgsp2EventType.name: cgsp2EventType
cgsp2EventType.description: The type of event history as follows. 'as' - Application Service 'asp' - Application Service Process 'mtp3' - Message Transport Protocol Level 3 'pc' - Point-code

cgsp2EventLoggedEvents.name: cgsp2EventLoggedEvents
cgsp2EventLoggedEvents.description: The number of events that have been logged.

cgsp2EventDroppedEvents.name: cgsp2EventDroppedEvents
cgsp2EventDroppedEvents.description: The number of events that could not be logged due to unavailable resources.

cgsp2EventMaxEntries.name: cgsp2EventMaxEntries
cgsp2EventMaxEntries.description: The upper limit on the number of events that the event history can contain. A value of 0 will prevent any event history from being retained. When this table is full, the oldest entry will be deleted as a new entry is added.

cgsp2EventMaxEntriesAllowed.name: cgsp2EventMaxEntriesAllowed
cgsp2EventMaxEntriesAllowed.description: This object specifies the maximum number of events that can be specified for cgsp2EventMaxEntries object.

cgsp2EventAsTable.name: cgsp2EventAsTable
cgsp2EventAsTable.description: A table of Application Service events generated per signalling point.

cgsp2EventAsTableEntry.name: cgsp2EventAsTableEntry
cgsp2EventAsTableEntry.description: An entry is added to this table for each application service event associated with a particular application service. The table contains the latest number of events defined by the cgsp2EventMaxEntries object. Once the table is full, the oldest entry is removed and a new entry is created to accommodate the new event.

cgsp2EventAsName.name: cgsp2EventAsName
cgsp2EventAsName.description: The application server name. This name has only local significance.

cgsp2EventAsIndex.name: cgsp2EventAsIndex
cgsp2EventAsIndex.description: Index into application service event history.

cgsp2EventAsText.name: cgsp2EventAsText
cgsp2EventAsText.description: A brief description of the application service event in text format.

cgsp2EventAsTimestamp.name: cgsp2EventAsTimestamp
cgsp2EventAsTimestamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the application service event was processed.

cgsp2EventAspTable.name: cgsp2EventAspTable
cgsp2EventAspTable.description: A table of application service process events generated per signalling point.

cgsp2EventAspTableEntry.name: cgsp2EventAspTableEntry
cgsp2EventAspTableEntry.description: An entry is added to this table for each application service process event associated with a particular application service process. The table contains the latest number of events defined by the cgsp2EventMaxEntries object. Once the table is full, the oldest entry is removed and a new entry is created to accommodate the new event.

cgsp2EventAspName.name: cgsp2EventAspName
cgsp2EventAspName.description: The application server process name. This name has only local significance.

cgsp2EventAspIndex.name: cgsp2EventAspIndex
cgsp2EventAspIndex.description: Index into application service process event history.

cgsp2EventAspText.name: cgsp2EventAspText
cgsp2EventAspText.description: A brief description of the application service process event in text format.

cgsp2EventAspTimestamp.name: cgsp2EventAspTimestamp
cgsp2EventAspTimestamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the application service process event was received.

cgsp2EventMtp3Table.name: cgsp2EventMtp3Table
cgsp2EventMtp3Table.description: A table of MTP3 events generated per signalling point.

cgsp2EventMtp3TableEntry.name: cgsp2EventMtp3TableEntry
cgsp2EventMtp3TableEntry.description: An MTP3 event that was previously generated by this signalling point. An entry is added to this table for each SS7 event generated on the managed system. The table contains the latest number of events defined by the cgsp2EventMaxEntries object. Once the table is full, the oldest entry is removed and a new entry is created to accommodate the new event.

cgsp2EventMtp3Text.name: cgsp2EventMtp3Text
cgsp2EventMtp3Text.description: A brief description of the SS7 event in text format. Each event provides information of state transitions specific to the MTP3 protocol.

cgsp2EventMtp3Timestamp.name: cgsp2EventMtp3Timestamp
cgsp2EventMtp3Timestamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the event was received by MTP3 layer.

cgsp2EventPcTable.name: cgsp2EventPcTable
cgsp2EventPcTable.description: A table of point-code events generated per signalling point.

cgsp2EventPcTableEntry.name: cgsp2EventPcTableEntry
cgsp2EventPcTableEntry.description: An entry is added to this table for each point-code event. The table contains the latest number of events defined by the cgsp2EventMaxEntries object. Once the table is full, the oldest entry is removed and a new entry is created to accommodate the new event.

cgsp2EventPcText.name: cgsp2EventPcText
cgsp2EventPcText.description: A brief description of the point-code event in text format.

cgsp2EventPcTimestamp.name: cgsp2EventPcTimestamp
cgsp2EventPcTimestamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the point-code event was received.

cgsp2QosTable.name: cgsp2QosTable
cgsp2QosTable.description: A table of information related to the defining Quality of Service to transport SS7 packets using SCTP/IP. Entries are added to this table via cgsp2QosRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatusconvention.

cgsp2QosTableEntry.name: cgsp2QosTableEntry
cgsp2QosTableEntry.description: Each entry define information relate to a Quality of Service class as needed to transport SS7 packets using SCTP/IP.

cgsp2QosClass.name: cgsp2QosClass
cgsp2QosClass.description: The quality of service class that can be defined to transport SS7 Packets using SCTP/IP.

cgsp2QosType.name: cgsp2QosType
cgsp2QosType.description: Enumerated list of QoS type that can be defined. A value ipPrecedence suggests that IP Type of Service (TOS) is based on cgsp2QosPrecedenceValue. A value ipDscp suggests that IP Type of Service (TOS) is based on cgsp2QosIpDscp.

cgsp2QosPrecedenceValue.name: cgsp2QosPrecedenceValue
cgsp2QosPrecedenceValue.description: A value to assign to the IP TOS bits in the IP datagram that carries one or more SS7 packets. The IP Precedence value is specified if cgsp2QosType is ipPrecedence, otherwise it is -1.

cgsp2QosIpDscp.name: cgsp2QosIpDscp
cgsp2QosIpDscp.reference: Differentiated Services is described and defined in the RFCs: 2474, 2475, 2597, and 2598.
cgsp2QosIpDscp.description: DiffServ CodePoint (DSCP) value to assign to the IP TOS bits in the IP datagram that carries one or more SS7 packets. DSCP provides scalable mechanisms to classify packets into groups or classes that have similar QoS requirements and then gives these groups the required treatment at every hop in the network. The DSCP value is specified if cgsp2QosType is ipDscp, otherwise it is -1.

cgsp2QosAclId.name: cgsp2QosAclId
cgsp2QosAclId.description: ITP Access lists can be used to use information specific to SS7 packets to assign an Qos class. A value of zero indicates that no access control list is present.

cgsp2QosRowStatus.name: cgsp2QosRowStatus
cgsp2QosRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cgsp2QosTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cgsp2LocalPeerTable.name: cgsp2LocalPeerTable
cgsp2LocalPeerTable.description: A local-peer table used establish SCTP associations. The port will be used to receive and sent requests to establish associations. Entries are added to this table via cgsp2LocalPeerRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cgsp2LocalPeerTableEntry.name: cgsp2LocalPeerTableEntry
cgsp2LocalPeerTableEntry.description: A list of attributes of the local-peer.

cgsp2LocalPeerPort.name: cgsp2LocalPeerPort
cgsp2LocalPeerPort.description: The local SCTP port for this local-peer. The value zero is not allowed.

cgsp2LocalPeerSlotNumber.name: cgsp2LocalPeerSlotNumber
cgsp2LocalPeerSlotNumber.description: This value is used to specify to which slot the local-peer will be offloaded. A value of negative one indicates the local-peer is not offloaded.

cgsp2LocalPeerRowStatus.name: cgsp2LocalPeerRowStatus
cgsp2LocalPeerRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete a row entry in cgsp2LocalPeerTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cgsp2LocalPeerProcessorNumber.name: cgsp2LocalPeerProcessorNumber
cgsp2LocalPeerProcessorNumber.description: This value is used to specify to which processor the local-peer will be offloaded on the line card indicated by cgsp2LocalPeerSlotNumber. For certain line cards like Flexwan, this value corresponds to bay number instead of processor number.

cgsp2LpIpAddrTable.name: cgsp2LpIpAddrTable
cgsp2LpIpAddrTable.description: A table of Local IP addresses group together to form the local-peer used to establish SCTP associations. For a given local-peer, there can be multiple local IP addresses which are used for the multi-homing feature of the SCTP associations. This table lists out the configured local IP addresses. Entries are added to this table via cgsp2LocalPeerRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cgsp2LpIpAddrTableEntry.name: cgsp2LpIpAddrTableEntry
cgsp2LpIpAddrTableEntry.description: A list of attributes of the Local IP addresses for the local-peer.

cgsp2LpIpAddressNumber.name: cgsp2LpIpAddressNumber
cgsp2LpIpAddressNumber.description: This object specifies the index for the instance's IP address.

cgsp2LpIpAddressType.name: cgsp2LpIpAddressType
cgsp2LpIpAddressType.description: This object contains the type of the local IP address used to create the association.

cgsp2LpIpAddress.name: cgsp2LpIpAddress
cgsp2LpIpAddress.description: This object contains the local IP address used to create association associations.

cgsp2LpIpAddressRowStatus.name: cgsp2LpIpAddressRowStatus
cgsp2LpIpAddressRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cgsp2LpIpAddrTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsTable.name: cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsTable
cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsTable.description: A table of MTP3 errors that have occurred on all Signalling Point supported by this device.

cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsTableEntry.name: cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsTableEntry
cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsTableEntry.description: A list of attributes used to provide a summary of the various MTP3 errors encountered by the device.

cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsType.name: cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsType
cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsType.description: This object specifies the index for the various error types.

cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsDescription.name: cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsDescription
cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsDescription.description: A brief description of the MTP3 error in text format.

cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsCount.name: cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsCount
cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsCount.description: Number of errors encountered for this type of MTP3 error as described in cgsp2Mtp3ErrorsDescription object.

cgsp2ContextTable.name: cgsp2ContextTable
cgsp2ContextTable.description: DCS(Data Collector Server) use ContextId as index to get additional information about the resource being monitoring. This table provides informations used to identify the resource(link or ASP).

cgsp2ContextEntry.name: cgsp2ContextEntry
cgsp2ContextEntry.description: Each entry (conceptual row) represents a resource(Link or ASP) that can be monitored by the the Probeless Monitor Feature. Each are added to deleted from this table as Link and ASP are configured.

cgsp2ContextIdentifier.name: cgsp2ContextIdentifier
cgsp2ContextIdentifier.description: The unique Id for LINK or ASP to Application

cgsp2ContextType.name: cgsp2ContextType
cgsp2ContextType.description: This object indicate the type of resource Link or ASP.

cgsp2ContextLinksetName.name: cgsp2ContextLinksetName
cgsp2ContextLinksetName.description: The name of the Linkset in which the link is configured and this object only applies when the cgsp2ContextType indicates the resource is a Link.

cgsp2ContextSlc.name: cgsp2ContextSlc
cgsp2ContextSlc.reference: ITU Q.704 Signalling network functions and messages. ANSI T1.111 Telecommunications - Signalling system No. 7 (SS7)-Message Transfer Part (MTP).
cgsp2ContextSlc.description: The Signalling Link Code for this link.This object only applies when the cgsp2ContextType indicates the resource is an Link.

cgsp2ContextAsName.name: cgsp2ContextAsName
cgsp2ContextAsName.description: The Aplication server name.This object only applies when the cgsp2ContextType indicates the resource is an ASP.

cgsp2ContextAspName.name: cgsp2ContextAspName
cgsp2ContextAspName.description: The Application Server Process Name.This object only applies when the cgsp2ContextType indicates the resource is an ASP.

cgsp2ContextNetworkName.name: cgsp2ContextNetworkName
cgsp2ContextNetworkName.description: The Network name configure for the instance in ITP

cgsp2OperMtp3Offload.name: cgsp2OperMtp3Offload
cgsp2OperMtp3Offload.description: Indicates location of MTP3 management function as follows. 'main' - MTP3 Management function operates only on main processor. 'offload' - MTP3 Management function operates on main processor and other available processors.

cgsp2OperRedundancy.name: cgsp2OperRedundancy
cgsp2OperRedundancy.description: The redundancy capability of devices for signalling points defined on this device as follows. 'none' - Device is not configured to support redundancy features. 'local' - Device provides redundancy by using backup processor on same device. 'distributed' - Device provides redundancy by using processors on two or more different physical device.

ciscoGsp2MIBCompliance.name: ciscoGsp2MIBCompliance
ciscoGsp2MIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO-ITP-GSP2-MIB.my MIB

ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev1.name: ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev1
ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev1.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO-ITP-GSP2-MIB.my MIB

ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev2.name: ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev2
ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO-ITP-GSP2-MIB.my MIB

ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev3.name: ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev3
ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev3.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO-ITP-GSP2-MIB.my MIB

ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev4.name: ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev4
ciscoGsp2MIBComplianceRev4.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO-ITP-GSP2-MIB.my MIB

ciscoGsp2LocalPeerGroupSup1.description: SS7 Local Peer supplemental object to ciscoGsp2LocalPeerGroup.
